Anniversary of Kim Jong Il's Start of Work at C.C., WPK Observed in Different Countries 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, June 19 (KCNA) -- Seminars, meetings, photo exhibitions and film shows were held by the Russian Youth Association for the Study of the Juche Idea, the Kim Il Sung Institute of Agricultural Science in Guinea and an international trading company of Malaysia from June 6 to 11 on the occasion of the 42nd anniversary of Kim Jong Il's start of work at the Central Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea.
 At a seminar on the work of Kim Jong Il "Giving Priority to Ideological Work Is Essential for Accomplishing Socialism", Dmitri Kostenko, chairman of the Russian Youth Association for the Study of the Juche Idea, and other speakers stressed that the work clarifies the importance and significance of the ideological work.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Banou Keita, director of the Guinean institute, said in his speech at a meeting that under the energetic and wise leadership of Kim Jong Il the WPK has strengthened into the party of President Kim Il Sung and displayed its might as a veteran and tested revolutionary party, a mother party faithfully serving the people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The president of the Malaysian company said that Kim Jong Il has devoted all his energies to the work for bringing a reunified country to the Korean people and expressed the belief that the Korean people would certainly reunify the country holding aloft the banner of the June 15 North-South Joint Declaration under his leadership. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A message of greetings to Kim Jong Il was adopted at the seminar held in Russia.

Swiss Organization Protests U.S. Financial Sanctions against DPRK 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, June 19 (KCNA) -- The Swiss Committee for Supporting Korea's Independent and Peaceful Reunification on June 9 sent a letter to the U.S. president in protest against the U.S. financial sanctions against the DPRK.
 The letter termed the sanctions criminal and aggressive act violating the international law, and contended that the rumor about "counterfeit notes" is a fig leaf for justifying the financial sanctions and covering up the crimes and human rights abuse of the U.S. worldwide. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Noting that the DPRK had nothing to do with the rumor of "counterfeit notes", the letter strongly urged the U.S. president to unconditionally and promptly lift the sanctions and return all the frozen assets to the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. government, the letter said, should fulfill its commitments and obligations and normalize the relations with the DPRK. Only then can the nuclear issue be settled and peaceful co-existence of the two countries be achieved.

Indian Organizations Support Korean People's Effort for Reunification 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, June 19 (KCNA) -- We extend active solidarity to the friendly Korean people in their effort to reunify the country in the idea of "By our nation itself", says the joint statement issued on June 13 by the Institute for the Foreign Policy Studies and four other organizations of India on the occasion of the sixth anniversary of the publication of the June 15 North-South Joint Declaration.
 The joint statement said the Songun politics is the only treasured sword defending sovereignty of the Korean nation and ensuring peace and reunification of the Korean Peninsula. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It went on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We strongly demand that the U.S. immediately withdraw its forces in south Korea who are disturbing implementation of the June 15 North-South Joint Declaration, icing the atmosphere of the north-south reconciliation, unity and reunification and gravely threatening world peace and security, give up its hostile policy towards the DPRK and stop at once its moves for a new war against it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In the future, we will conduct more vigorous solidarity activities for encouraging the Korean people in the efforts to implement the June 15 joint declaration, in unison with the progressive forces in different countries valuing world peace and security and supporting Korea's reunification.

Rodong Sinmun Calls for Upholding Songun Banner 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, June 19 (KCNA) -- Rodong Sinmun today dedicates an editorial to the 42nd anniversary of Kim Jong Il's start of work at the Central Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea.
 Kim Jong Il is a great leader who recorded the long history of his leadership of revolution as one of the most brilliant victories and miracles of the century, gifted with rare great man's traits and qualities previously unknown in history, says the daily in the editorial, a summary of which reads: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A fundamental turn was brought in party building and overall party work under the energetic leadership of Kim Jong Il who has always put greatest efforts in strengthening the party and steadily increasing its leading role. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He has created the model of the times in succeeding the idea and cause of the leader under the banner of modeling the whole society on the Juche idea, reared our revolutionary armed forces into an invincible strong army and built so many great monumental edifices of the Workers' Party era all over the country, and words fail to describe all the immortal feats he has performed in those days. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The cause of the Party is the cause of the Songun revolution and the history of his revolutionary leadership is resplendent as a noble history in which Kim Jong Il has created an ever- victorious heroic epic under the Songun banner. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is entirely a brilliant fruition of his Songun politics that the lifeline of the Korean revolution pioneered in Mt. Paektu has been steadily succeeded and the dignity and unconquerable features of socialist Korea have been strikingly demonstrated to the world despite the ceaseless war provocation moves of the imperialists and complicated political situation of the world. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is a miracle in history that he firmly defended the banner of socialism and opened a new era of building a great prosperous powerful nation with the original Songun policy in the last decade of the 20th century when the Korean revolution faced a grim test. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The whole party, whole army and all the people should more firmly arm with the greatness of the Songun policy of Kim Jong Il, unite ever closer around the headquarters of the revolution, holding ever higher the slogan "Let us defend the revolutionary headquarters headed by the great Comrade Kim Jong Il with our lives!" and resolutely defend his undying leadership exploits in party building and thoroughly apply them to the party work and activity.

Anniversary of Kim Jong Il's Work Marked 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, June 19 (KCNA) -- Rodong Sinmun Monday dedicates an article to the 9th anniversary of Kim Jong Il's famous work "On Preserving the Juche Character and National Character of the Revolution and Construction".
 The work, published on June 19, Juche 86 (1997), reviewed the history and experience of struggle of the Workers' Party of Korea and people who had resolutely preserved the Juche character and national character. It clarified the matters of defending a patriotic stand, carrying on revolution and construction in Korean way, strengthening the revolutionary driving force and enhancing national pride of the people. It gave an overall exposition of tasks and ways to preserve the Juche character and nation character of the revolution and construction and build a powerful and prosperous country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Jong Il has wisely led the struggle to firmly defend the sovereignty of the country and the nation and give full play to the advantage of the Korean nation with his energetic Songun revolutionary leadership, the article says, and goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The wisdom of leadership of Kim Jong Il who has preserved and glorified the Juche character and national character can be found in settling all the issues arising in the revolution and construction in Korean way on the principle of national independence. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He has developed in depth the Songun idea based on the principle of Songun that arms mean revolution and a victory of socialism to suit the conditions of the times in which the anti-imperialist struggle was getting fiercer and the conditions and environment of the revolutionary struggle changed, and thoroughly applied it to the revolution and construction. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean people have the firm conviction that there is nothing fearful and impossible as long as they are united close around him in one-mind and have an invincible revolutionary army. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We are building a great prosperous powerful socialist nation our own way however flagrant the anti-DPRK campaign of the U.S. imperialists may be and whatever ordeals and difficulties may stand in our way.  It is the revolutionary confidence and pluck of the Korean army and people to see who laughs last. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The wisdom of his leadership is also found in the fact that he has got the legacy of the nation preserved and brought the advantage of the nation into full play to remarkably enhance the national pride of the Korean people and led the whole nation to turn out in the drive for national reunification and prosperity in the idea of patriotism, the article concludes.

All Koreans Called upon to Implement June 15 Joint Declaration 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, June 19 (KCNA) -- The historic summit in Pyongyang and the publication of the June 15 North-South Joint Declaration marked historic events as they strikingly demonstrated the Korean nation' firm will for independent reunification internally and externally and ushered in a new era of national independence and reunification. The June 15 era of reunification shines as an era of the unity and reunification of the Korean nation. 
 Rodong Sinmun Monday says this in a signed article. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The June 15 era of reunification is an era in which "By our nation itself", the idea of national independence and unity, guides the national history and in which the Koreans are promoting the common interests of the nation through wide-range cooperation and exchange between the north and the south. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They have smashed the vicious obstructive moves of the anti-reunification forces at home and abroad through national cooperation guided by the idea of "By our nation itself" over the last several years. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The wide-ranging exchange and cooperation between the north and the south in different fields including various fabrics of social life such as politics, economy, culture and sports firmly convinced the Koreans of the truth that they have the same blood, history, culture and tradition and if they distrust each other and stand in confrontation with each other, this will only do harm to themselves and give foreign forces a chance to fish in troubled waters. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The June 15 era of reunification is an era of a nationwide movement for reunification as it calls on all the fellow countrymen to work together to bring earlier the day of reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The will and stamina of the Koreans to achieve the independent reunification of the nation have been strikingly demonstrated by grand festivals for national reunification held with splendor with representatives of political parties and social organizations, figures and people of all strata of the north and the south and Korean overseas attending and inter-Korean meetings of people from all walks of life including workers, peasants, youth and students held in Pyongyang, Seoul and Mt. Kumgang resort one after another since the adoption of the June 15 joint declaration. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The All-Korean Committee for Implementation of June 15 Joint Declaration formed as a permanent organization of the solidarity movement for national reunification last year is functioning as an umbrella body for solidarity among Koreans in the north and the south and overseas.

Immortal Feats Performed by Kim Jong Il in Leadership over Party 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, June 19 (KCNA) -- General Secretary Kim Jong Il started his work at the Central Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea on the 19th of June 42 years ago.
 Epochal changes have been since effected in the work of the WPK and the revolutionary development and a new era of great creation and change has been ushered in. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Jong Il has given clear-cut answers to all the theoretical and practical issues arising in strengthening the WPK to be Kim Il Sung's Party for ever. The issues ranges from the work to hold President Kim Il Sung in high esteem to the fundamental principles and methods of Party building and activities, the unity and cohesion of the Party, Juche-oriented Party work system and methods and the guidance to the Party life of the members. And he has wisely led the efforts for realizing them. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He put forward the program on Party building for imbuing the Juche idea into the whole party and society and took revolutionary measures for strengthening the Party organizationally and ideologically. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He has authored many famous works to brightly light the orientation and ways for the Party building and work. Among them are "On Further Improving Party Ideological Work," "On the Fundamentals of Revolutionary Party Building" and "Giving Priority to Ideological Work is Essential for Accomplishing Socialism." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The years are shining with his great efforts to defend the revolutionary tradition as the life-line of the Korean revolution. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Under his guidance, statues of the President have been erected in different parts of the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 While making a long inspection tour of army units, he visited the revolutionary battle sites of Mt. Paektu and other places to intensify the education in the revolutionary traditions. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Jong Il ushered in the heyday in the economic, cultural and other fields. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He defined the principle of speed campaign, which was created in the 1960s when he led the work of the literary and art fields, as the main form of the socialist construction and initiated many mass movements such as 70-day campaign, a 100-day campaign, Three-revolution Red Flag Movement and the Campaign to Follow the Example of the Unassuming Heroes. As a result, world-startling miracles and innovations have been worked out in all the fields of the economic construction. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A large Oxygen Separator and a 10,000ton press were manufactured and many monumental edifices including the world leading West Sea Barrage, the Tower of Juche Idea and the Arch of Triumph were built in a campaign to create the speed of the 80's following the spirit displayed in the 1970s. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A lot of creations have been constructed in the 1990s and in the new century even under the unspeakable difficulties and trials. Among them are power stations, modernized and special factories, stock-farms, Kwangmyongsong Saltern, Youth Hero Motorway and the Kaechon-Lake Thaesong and Paekma-Cholsan Waterways. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The arable land has been realigned to suit the socialist countryside of Korea and innovations taken place in the farming. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Proud successes have been registered in the construction of socialist culture, too. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The mass gymnastic and artistic display "Arirang," which was the acme of the "Renaissance in the 20th century", the launch of the artificial satellite "Kwangmyongsong-1" which powerfully demonstrated the might of the socialist Korea, the construction of recreation grounds including Mt. Chilbo and Ryongmun Cavern and the brisk mass artistic activities substantiate the wise guidance of Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In particular, the last ten-odd years takes a special position in the history of his 40-odd year leadership over the Party. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In those days, he creditably defended the destiny of socialist Korea with his unique Songun politics and invariably upheld the revolutionary red flag as the President did in his lifetime. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Indeed, over the last four decades, he has performed undying revolutionary exploits for the eternal prosperity of the Kim Il Sung's nation.

Chongsaengsu, Medicinal Water 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, June 19 (KCNA) -- Chongsaengsu good for health is being mass-produced in the Democratic People's Republic of Korea.
 It is medicinal water which contains over 80 kinds of natural elements including Se and microelements. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The water promotes excretion of various kinds of organic and inorganic poisonous substances accumulated in the human body and thus to boost normal function of the internal organs and hemopoietic and endocrine system. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It also neutralizes poison by alcohol, chemical medicines, poisonous mushrooms, gas and pollution and increases the appetites. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is applicable to the treatment of hepatitis, pancreatitis, gastroenteritis, diabetes, nephritis, pyelitis, hypertension, arteriosclerosis, myocarditis, myocardial infraction, leucopenia and cancerous diseases and the prevention from the radiation damage. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In particular, the water helps the growth and intellectual development of children, raises their immunity function, makes the elders full of vigor and prevents aging. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Years of its clinical test shows special curing effect. The demand for the water, which was awarded a state patent, is on an ever increase.

Kim Jong Il Enjoys Art Performance Given by KPA Art Squad
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, June 19 (KCNA) -- General Secretary Kim Jong Il together with servicepersons enjoyed a performance given by an art squad of KPA Unit 287.
 Its members put on the stage colorful numbers of various genres including chorus "Peerless Patriot General Kim Jong Il," agitation on the basis of a revolutionary anecdote "Army Loved and Trusted More Than Others ", solo "Blessed My Life", witty talk "Let's Thoroughly Establish the Army Discipline," female quintet "Yeppuni", poem and story-telling "Let's Not Slacken Our Vigilance Even a Moment" and chorus "For the Motherland".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
He highly praised the members of the art squad of the unit for their successful performance and extended his thanks to them, expressing great satisfaction over the fact that they have created art pieces suited to the servicepersons' thoughts and feelings and presented a truthful and popular performance. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is very important to conduct performing art with great influence and strong appeal in the ideological education of the servicepersons, he said, indicating important tasks to be tackled to intensify it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Among the audience were KPA Generals Ri Myong Su, Hyon Chol Hae, Pak Jae Gyong and other general officers.

Japan's Hostile Act against DPRK Blasted
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, June 19 (KCNA) -- Vice-chairman of the Central Standing Committee of the General Association of Korean Residents in Japan (Chongryon) Nam Sung U issued a statement on June 16 assailing the House of Councilors of the Japanese Diet for approving a bill on handling the "abduction issue" and "other human rights abuses by north Korea", according to KNS from Tokyo.
 The passage of the bill is a very hostile act as it is not only an infringement upon the dignity and sovereignty of the DPRK but is aimed at laying an international siege to the DPRK to bring it down, pursuant to the U.S. hostile policy toward it, he said, and went on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The bill is also a breach of the basic spirit of the DPRK-Japan Pyongyang Declaration in which Japan committed itself to settle its inglorious past and normalize bilateral relations. It also throws another stumbling block in the efforts to improve the bilateral relations. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The reactionary conservative forces of Japan have persistently used abduction and human rights issues for their political purposes, far from exerting sincere efforts for the implementation of the declaration since its publication. They have instead incited hostility toward the DPRK and put sanctions and pressure upon it, virtually pushing the bilateral relations to the lowest ebb. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It was against this backdrop that new regulations on the portcall of Mangyongbong-92 was enforced although it serves the humanitarian purpose of helping Koreans in Japan visit their homeland and unwarranted searches of institutions related to Chongryon were perpetrated and fixed property taxes were levied upon them under the pretext of "strict application of the existing law".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The rights of the Koreans in Japan should be protected as they suffered exploitation and big sacrifices under the colonial rule of Japan. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is clear that the bill is bound to threaten the elementary rights and right to existence of the Koreans in Japan including their freedom to visit homeland and restrict their business activities and intensify the suppression and exploitation of them. The bill is, therefore, intolerable. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The enforcement of such hostile and provocative bill to increase the pressure upon the DPRK would becloud the prospect of solving pending issues between the DPRK and Japan and exacerbate the tension between them. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Nam Sung U urged the Japanese authorities to roll up their hostile policy toward the DPRK, halt their suppression of Koreans in Japan and the unwarranted enforcement of regulations against them and sincerely implement the DPRK-Japan Pyongyang Declaration.
